import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Read data from CSV file
data = pd.read_csv('seattle_weather_1948-2017.csv')  

# Convert 'DATE' column to datetime format
data['DATE'] = pd.to_datetime(data['DATE'])

# Use .loc[] to set 'YEAR' column
data.loc[:, 'YEAR'] = data['DATE'].dt.year

# Filter data for years where max temperature > 26 and min temperature < 20
filtered_data = data[(data['TMAX'] > 26) & (data['TMIN'] < 20)]

# Group by year and count occurrences
yearly_counts = filtered_data.groupby('YEAR').size()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Assuming 'data' is your DataFrame containing temperature and precipitation columns

# Calculate average temperature and precipitation by year
yearly_avg = data.groupby('YEAR').agg({'TMAX': 'mean', 'PRCP': 'mean'}).reset_index()

# Separate features (temperature) and target (precipitation)
X = yearly_avg[['TMAX']]
y = yearly_avg['PRCP']

# Create and fit the linear regression model
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X, y)

# Make predictions
predictions = model.predict(X)

# Plot the data points
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.scatter(yearly_avg['TMAX'], yearly_avg['PRCP'], label='Data', color='blue')

# Plot the regression line
plt.plot(X, predictions, label='Linear Regression', color='red')

plt.title('Relationship between Average Temperature and Precipitation by Year')
plt.xlabel('Average Temperature (C)')
plt.ylabel('Average Precipitation')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

The scatter plot with the regression line illustrates the relationship between average temperature and precipitation by year. Each point represents a year's average temperature and precipitation, while the regression line shows the overall trend in the data. The upward or downward slope of the line indicates the direction of the relationship: a positive slope suggests that as temperature increases, so does precipitation, while a negative slope implies the opposite. This visualization provides insights into how temperature influences precipitation patterns over time, aiding in understanding climate dynamics.
